Author: bunni54
Text: I find it hard to stop when you have counted for so long, it's almost hardwired into you and you can't forget the information you've already taught yourself. I try really hard not to but it's like my brain calculator is on autopilot 24/7. Would love to learn how to make that stop, almost like i need to eat an entirely new diet of new foods where I never look at a nutrition label.

Author: algorthin
Text: I've been trying really hard to not calorie count and when I don't do it I do a lot better but hoo man.
